$interpreted: Hestia: Are you sure this is the way to Atlas, Puggi? I'm sure we've been past here already...
Puggi: Please, I'm the hero of this arc. Destiny's star burns bright above my head, and it's telling me we're right on track!
Hestia: Can you be serious for just one moment! Nigel's gonna be so worried. I'll have to ask whoever we come across to deliver a message for us.
Puggi: I am serious, just keep up with me! Puggi!
Hestia: Wow, there's an enormous flower growing here~
Puggi: ...Hmm? Why's it look so familiar...
Hestia: It moved!?
Puggi: I remember now! Aren't you the mid-tier boss Pang and I did away with easily back in Season 1!?
Puggi: Wait! Don't you belong in Whistlewood Valley? So you can move about now, too?
Hestia: Maybe it's to do with those monsters influencing the environment.
Puggi: Fiddlesticks! If only that were true! Screenwriter, get yourself out here, now! You think you can save on costs by messing about with me!?
Hestia: Behind you, Puggi!
Hestia: Puggi!!!!
Puggi: Surprised!? I'm not the person I was before!
Puggi: I beat you once, and I'll do it all over again! Let's go, Hestia! We're ending this once and for all!
Hestia: ...Attacking's totally futile, Puggi, what'll we do?
Puggi: So, you've been training yourself up too, eh? Fine, you asked for it!
Puggi: Even if you're the final boss of all time, you'll never be able to fend off my ultimate move. Supercalifragilâ€”
Puggi: Run!!!!!
Hestia: I thought you had an ultimate move!?
Puggi: Gah! The MC has to survive before he can win!
Fredrica: So will the man with the horns see us once he's all finished?
Yamitsuki: ......
Yamitsuki: (...Nigel must have been back to Atlas since I last heard from him... But...)
Lio: Can you help us out with Nigel, Fredrica? Angelia's waiting for our return...
Leah: No way, that bozo better come greet us in person!
Leah: Why should she get to see him first? And then us chasing at their heels. That's not fair!
Yamitsuki: (I can't hide this any longer... Where are you, Nigel...)
Fredrica: Miss Rabbit, please don't make a scene. I guess the man with the horns simply isn't in Atlas?
Leah: Not here? Is that right, Eve?
Yamitsuki: No, Nigel's...
Fredrica: Oh dear. It's written all over your face.
Leah: That idiot! How could he run off at a time like this!
Fredrica: Who knows. Men need their own space too, sometimes. But I'm afraid this means I'll have to ask you to step in as leader, Miss Yamitsuki.
Puggi: Save us!!! Where's everybody gone to!?
Yamitsuki: Are they being attacked by a flower...? Don't let it into Atlas!
Fredrica: All right, all right. I'll teach it a lesson, just so we can talk in peace.
Puggi: Puggggiii~ Told ya I was the bees' knees~
Leah: Could this get any worse? What's that fat bird sticking his beak into now!
Jerome: Are you okay, Miss?
Hestia: I'm fine, thanks to you.
Fredrica: Even the flowers of Whistlewood Valley are out on the make now. Don't you think this is getting out of hand, Miss Yamitsuki?
Yamitsuki: Well...
Hestia: You're Yamitsuki?
Yamitsuki: Hm? That's me.
Hestia: Great, we've finally found you!
Hestia: Nigel wanted us to give this to you.
Yamitsuki: (This is... Nigel's scarf!)
Yamitsuki: Please, give me that letter!
Lio: Did something happen to Nigel, Miss Eve?
Yamitsuki: He's... been held up outside the Desert Kingdom port...
Lio: The Desert Kingdom? So that's where he's gone to? That can't be right, wouldn't he be in grave danger!?
Yamitsuki: ...General Lucien.
Fredrica: Yes~ I'm listening~
Yamitsuki: ...Atlas will open the port and assist you with resettling the refugees.
Yamitsuki: But there's one condition. The Kingdom of the Sun must negotiate with the Desert Kingdom for Nigel's protection and safe return.
Leah: Miss Eve...
Fredrica: I knew it, you've got a heart of gold after all~
Fredrica: All right, understood~ I'll go back and report to Her Majesty right away.
Jerome: We should get going, too.
Yamitsuki: (Am I doing the right thing, Nigel...)
